---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const updated = 'April 2026';
---
<Layout title="Terms of Service — Worflo" description="Worflo terms of service.">
  <div style="max-width:720px;margin:0 auto;padding:64px 24px 80px">
    <p class="section-eyebrow">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="section-title">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p style="color:var(--gray-5);font-size:13px;margin-bottom:40px">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <div style="font-size:15px;color:var(--gray-7);line-height:1.8;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:32px">
      <div>
        <h2 style="font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);margin-bottom:10px">1. Acceptance</h2>
        <p>By connecting your HubSpot account to Worflo, you agree to these terms. If you are using Worflo on behalf of an organisation, you represent that you have authority to bind that organisation.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 style="font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);margin-bottom:10px">2. Service description</h2>
        <p>Worflo provides workflow version control, execution tracing, error monitoring, and related tools for HubSpot. The service is provided as-is. We make no warranties about uptime or fitness for a specific purpose beyond what is stated in your plan's SLA (Enterprise only).</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 style="font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);margin-bottom:10px">3. Your responsibilities</h2>
        <p>You are responsible for maintaining the security of your Worflo account credentials. You must not use Worflo to store, transmit, or process sensitive personal data beyond what is required to operate your HubSpot workflows. You must comply with HubSpot's own terms of service.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 style="font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);margin-bottom:10px">4. Billing</h2>
        <p>Paid plans are billed monthly via Stripe. You may cancel at any time; access continues until the end of the current billing period. We reserve the right to change pricing with 30 days' notice. Refunds are handled on a case-by-case basis — contact support within 7 days of a charge if you believe it was made in error.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 style="font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);margin-bottom:10px">5. Limitations of liability</h2>
        <p>Worflo is not liable for any indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from your use of the service, including but not limited to workflow errors, missed automations, or data loss. Our total liability is limited to the amount you paid in the 3 months preceding the claim.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 style="font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);margin-bottom:10px">6. Termination</h2>
        <p>We may suspend or terminate accounts that violate these terms, engage in abuse, or have outstanding payment failures. You may terminate your account at any time from the Settings page or by emailing support.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 style="font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);margin-bottom:10px">7. Governing law</h2>
        <p>These terms are governed by the laws of New South Wales, Australia. Disputes will be resolved in NSW courts.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 style="font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:var(--dark);margin-bottom:10px">8. Contact</h2>
        <p><a href="mailto:support@worflo.io">support@worflo.io</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
